description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for applications from enthusiastic individuals to work within our busy theatre complex. We are looking for experienced Theatre Practitioners, including Registered Nurses and Operating Department Practitioners for full and part time positions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have 17 operating theatres distributed over four suites on this site, and cover both elective and emergency surgery in the following specialities; gynaecology, orthopaedics, urology, vascular, colorectal, breast, endocrine, and upper GI. We have the latest technology including the da Vinci Robot and we run a 24/7 emergency operating service (CPOD). Our staff are our greatest asset and we believe that supporting our workforce to grow, develop and innovate creates a great place to work and enables us to provide excellent care and compassion to our patients. Excellent training opportunities are provided with external and internal development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for experienced individuals who will enjoy working as part of the multidisciplinary team, and you should be proficient in scrub / anaesthetics. Theatre is a fast paced environment where a positive attitude, energy and innovation are welcomed. Successful candidates must be able to work various shift patterns and be fully flexible in order to cover comprehensive 24 hour surgical service. Any applicants wishing to visit the department prior to applying or interview would be welcome to make contact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ensure you take the time to tell us in your supporting evidence why you would be right for this post in theatres&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Royal Bournemouth and Christchurch Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust and Poole Hospital NHS Foundation Trust merged in 2020 to form East Dorset Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: 1st December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rachel francis Clincial leader rachel.francis@uhd.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone Main Reception -Theatres 0300 019 4183 or 0300 019 4432&lt;/p&gt;
